<table class="drug-table data-table table table-condensed table-bordered"><tbody><tr id="identification"><th class="divider" colspan="2">Identification</th></tr><tr><th>Name</th><td><strong>Cisplatin</strong></td></tr><tr><th>Accession Number</th><td><strong>DB00515</strong>&#160; (APRD00359)</td></tr><tr><th>Type</th><td>small molecule</td></tr><tr><th>Groups</th><td>approved</td></tr><tr><th>Description</th><td><p>Cisplatin, cisplatinum or cis-diamminedichloroplatinum(II) (<span class="caps">CDDP</span>) is a platinum-based chemotherapy drug used to treat various types of cancers, including sarcomas, some carcinomas (e.g. small cell lung cancer, and ovarian cancer), lymphomas and germ cell tumors. It was the first member of its class, which now also includes carboplatin and oxaliplatin.</p></td></tr><tr><th>Structure</th><td><div class="structure"><a class="moldbi-thumbnail" href="http://structures.wishartlab.com/molecules/DB00515/image.png"><img alt="Thumb" src="http://structures.wishartlab.com/molecules/DB00515/thumb.png"></a></div><div class="structure-links"><div class="btn-group btn-group-xs"><a class="btn btn-default" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00515.mol">MOL</a><a class="btn btn-default" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00515.sdf">SDF</a><a class="btn btn-default" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00515.pdb">PDB</a><a class="btn btn-default" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00515.smiles">SMILES</a><a class="btn btn-default" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00515.inchi">InChI</a><a class="btn btn-info" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00515">View Structure</a></div></div></td></tr><tr><th>Synonyms</th><td class="data-table-container"><table class="table table-condensed table-striped datatable" id="synonyms"><thead><th>Synonym</th><th>Language</th><th>Code</th></thead><tbody><tr><td>CDDP</td><td><span class="wishart wishart-not-available">Not